@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Urban Workers**: Consisting of blue-collar workers in factories, workshops, mines, et cetera. Most are socialists, supporting the PSI or any other communist faction. They make up about 20 to 25% of the population.

**Small Business Owners**: Consisting of shopkeepers, artisans, small business workers and the like. They are divided between the Catholic Parties, Liberal Parties and a small minority to the PSI. They make up about 15-20% of the population.

**Rural Workers & Farmers**: Consisting of those who lived in the unindustrialised south who work as farmers, agricultural workers, et cetera. They are fairly evenly split between the PSI and the Catholic Parties of the UECI & CC. They make up about 50% of the population.

**Industralists & Landowners**: Consisting of the elite holding significant economic power. They are the bedrock of the liberal parties, seeing them as stable and protecting their wealth, though some more religious prefer the Catholic parties. They make up about 5-10% of the population.

**Veterans & Unemployed**: Consisting of veterans who felt betrayed by the government for their gains in the First World War. They are fierce supporters of nationalist and fascist movements, though some opted to support the PSI instead. They make up about 5% of the population.

**Catholics**: Consisting of the clergy and those religious to the Catholic Church. They support the Catholic parties almost entirely, making up a strong foundation for the UECI & CC. They make up about 5% of the population.


